The elderly woman has a health condition that can be modeled by a function incorporating a system of differential equations. This function expresses the state of her health conditions as a function of time and the treatment efforts by the retired doctor. The function can be written as follows:

\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned}
\frac{dH}{dt} = aH - bH^2 - cT \\
\frac{dT}{dt} = dH - eT 
\end{aligned}
\end{equation}

Where $H$ represents the health of the woman, $T$ represents the treatment efforts by the doctor, and $a$, $b$, $c$, $d$, and $e$ are positive constants. 

Assuming the initial conditions $H(0) = H_0$ and $T(0) = T_0$, find the general solutions to the system of differential equations.
